{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Modified version of X-Raym's "X-Raym_Add point on envelopes at edit cursor.lua"; instead of just adding a point for the momentary value along the existing envelope curve, this script adds a point for the current value of the parameter. The use case is latch-preview mode, if the user makes a change she likes and wants to print it as a point to the automation lane at the time under the edit cursor.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Inspired by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://youtu.be/HEVKLiWkRkk"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Kenny Gioia's "Razor Edit - Fast Mode in REAPER"
}}}
, this script makes the appropriate changes to the Mouse Modifier preferences to support fast Razor Editing. Improved over what Kenny can do using standard actions is that the shift-modified left-drag actions are incorporated with the "ignoring snap" action variants.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The workflow is also simpler, as it's just a single toggle script. It can be hooked up to a key command and/or a toolbar button.\par}
}
